data.name: Stuffed Bell Peppers with Black Beans and Avocado Cream
data.quickTastyDescription: Colorful bell peppers filled with a savory black bean mix, topped with a creamy avocado sauce for a refreshing finish.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds.
In a bowl, combine black beans, corn, cooked rice, cumin, chili powder, salt, and pepper.
Stuff the mixture into each bell pepper until they are full.
Place the stuffed peppers in a baking dish and cover with foil. Bake for 25 minutes.
While the peppers are baking, prepare the avocado cream by blending avocado, Greek yogurt, lime juice, and a pinch of salt until smooth.
After 25 minutes, remove the foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes to slightly brown the tops.
Serve the peppers warm, drizzled with avocado cream and garnished with fresh cilantro.
data.detailedName: Stuffed Bell Peppers with Black Beans and Avocado Cream
